    <h2>Retrieving VARCAP Forecasts</h2>
    <p>The forecast files in this directory have names that follow the WP-MIP conventions as:</p>
    <pre>
      FILESTR
    </pre>
    <p>They can be retrieved from the Linux command line using a command based on the example below, where LEV_INST 2-digit months (MM) can be
      specified as needed (e.g. as variables or literals) or provided as wildcards to download multiple files:</p>

    <pre>
      LEV_EXAMPLE
      mm=03
      wget -e robots=off -nd -r --no-parent -A "LEV_WILD*_${mm}.grib2" https://hpfx.collab.science.gc.ca/~swpm001/WP-MIP/VARPATH/
    </pre>
      
    
